Hitachi Ltd &lt;HIT.T> expects to achieveits parent company sales estimate of 2,900 billion yen in theyear ending March 31, helped by high general-use ultra-largecomputer sales and despite the higher-than-expected yen.    Current profits are unlikely to reach the estimated 90billion yen as the currency's rise has reduced the value offoreign bond holdings, but the company will retain a nine yendividend for 1986/87, a spokesman said.    Current profits in the year to end-March 1986 fell 38.2 pctfrom a year before to 158.04 billion yen on sales of 3,003billion, down 0.8 pct, mainly due to the yen's appreciation. REUTER&#3;